+//! Ngram Speculation Cache
+//!
+//! Caches common token sequences to enable speculative decoding without a draft model.
+//! When the current context matches a cached prefix, we speculatively accept the
+//! cached continuation and verify in a single batch decode.
+//!
+//! This is memory-efficient (typically <50MB) and provides 1.2-1.5x speedup
+//! for repetitive patterns like code boilerplate.
+//!
+//! How it works:
+//! 1. Track recent token sequences and their continuations
+//! 2. When generating, check if last N tokens match a cached prefix
+//! 3. If match, propose K continuation tokens for batch verification
+//! 4. Accept tokens until first mismatch
+//!
+//! Example: If we've seen "def __init__(self" → "): \n" multiple times,
+//! next time we see "def __init__(self", we speculatively generate "): \n"
+
